manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: German Engineering - German Design - German Quality - German Performance Highly Efficient Operation Straight Power 12 is a future-proof ATX 3.0 power supply with 80 PLUS Platinum certification and virtually inaudible operation. Future-Proof Your System Straight Power 12 is an ATX 3.0 PSU that comes with both native integration of the 12VHPWR connector for next-generation PCIe 5.0 graphics cards, and 4 PCIe 6+2-pin connectors for support of current-gen GPUs. This makes the PSU extremely versatile and the perfect choice for powerful systems of today and the ones to come. The New Standard of Power Straight Power 12 offers continuous power with one massive 12V rail. Even if the graphics card demands excessive power for a short time: the Straight Power 12 handles power excursions up to double its rated power with ease. This ensures reliable operation with the next generation of processors and graphics cards.

German Engineering - German Design - German Quality - German Performance Flawless Cooling Design The funnel-shaped fan inlet of the Straight Power 12 increases airflow while reducing unwanted turbulence for a higher cooling performance. The wire-free design inside allows the cool air to reach all components which ultimately leads to a longer lifespan. State-Of-The-Art Technologies With full bridge LLC Straight Power 12 offers advanced technologies, resulting in higher efficiency, better regulation, and lower ripple noise for an incomparably stable operation. Silent Wings 4 Fan The high-end Silent Wings fan delivers best-of-class airflow yet produces very little noise. This is thanks to its unique, optimized fan blade design along with an advanced fluid-dynamic bearing and 6-pole fan motor that largely eliminates operational noise, has a super-long life and minimal power consumption.

Japanese 105° Capacitors Only premium components are used in Straight Power 12. That is why this PSU features exclusively high-quality Japanese capacitors. They are rated at 105°C for stability, reliability, and a long operating life. Convenience and Connectivity Modular, sleeved cables of up to 100cm in length simplify component installation and reduce annoying clutter. This results in increased airflow and improved cooling - even in the largest PC cases.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quiet and stable
reviews.reviewText: I've had this power supply for about 2 weeks now and so far so good, its stable and quiet. The atx 3.0 cable really tidies up the installation with only one cable going to the gpu. I've ran many games with no issues. I cant hear the power supply at all and the price is great. Would recommend as this is my first be quiet! product I've purchased.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very quiet, works as expected!!
reviews.reviewText: This was only $10 more than the 1000w when I bought it, though, id imagine the other straight power be quiet power supplys would also be identical. Anyways, its as quiet as can be. works as youd expect a power supply to work. Comes with cables to fill ALL ports!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Power supply lives up to its namesake

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I purchased the 1200w straight power from BeQuiet. Ya know what, it sure is quiet! The build quality is excellent. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 11, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The best power supply for a test bench HANDS DOWN!
reviews.reviewText: I have owned a few different brand PSU's over the last 20 or so years and always tended to go with Seasonic for there longevity. My last one went strong for about 8 years before starting to lose 5v stability recently. So I figured I would just go Seasonic again but decided to do a little shopping around first. I had always heard good things about be quiet CPU heatsinks and fans being very reliable and super quiet but had never owned anything from them. So after watching some reviews and reading a bunch about them I decided to give one a go. I have a Praxis Wetbench (PC test bench) that has nothing to block any fan noise which is always a challenge when dealing with a test bench config. I have my system filly liquid cooled and some very quiet fans on my radiator but my Seasonic PSU was always the loudest part of my setup. To the point where when at full load benchmarking or gaming it would sound like a hair dryer and was always a bit annoying. Over the years I guess I just got used to it and debt with it. But with this be queit let me tell you.. THIS THING IS NEAR SILENT! Even when pushing it pretty hard it never gets louder them my radiator fans and they are very quiet. I cannot put into words how peaceful my office is now. Its wonderful! I cannot speak to be quiet's longevity but I can definitely say its by far, the quietest PSU I have ever used and the build quality seems very good. Also come with very pliable sleeved cables. Much better then the flat black one you get with Corsair, Thermaltake, Coolermaster and multitude of other brands. Hoping for many years of use. Love it so far!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This supply is great. However, the inrush current into this beast at power-up is so high that it brings the line voltage down far enough to momentarily trip my Cyber Power UPS...but only if the line voltage is 118v or below. If it's 119 or higher, the UPS won't trip. I tried to configure the UPS for a lower trip voltage, but it was already at the minimum of 80 volts. As well, I've got a huge tower case with the power supply mounted at the bottom and the motherboard 24-pin and two 8-pin cpu connectors are at the top edge of the vertically mounted board...and yet the cables that come with this supply are long enough...sweet!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Worked well for a year!
reviews.reviewText: I didn't write a review when I first purchased this power supply nor when this power supply failed but I decided it was time to do so now. I purchased this power supply around Sep 2021 as part of several other items needed to rebuild my desktop. It installed fairly easily and it did come with plenty of connector cables.While it was in use the loudest parts of my computer were the cooling fans (still are). When it failed almost 11 months later. Unfortunately, I couldn't wait for the whole return/test/fail/replace scenario to play out and purchased another beQuiet power supply a day later (I had to get the 11 Platinum 1200w since it was the only one available for next day delivery).I finally got around to mailing off the broken supply in April 2023. I was notified April 21 that the facility had received my item. It is now May 2nd, 2023 and my replacement power supply was delivered today. I am pleased with the fairly quick turn around .. I just wish it was more like a broken cell phone .. they ship you the replacement FIRST and if you fail to send the broken item back they charge you for it.If I can find someone who wants to buy a new Straight Power 11 Platinum 1000W power supply I can offset some of my costs, since I don't expect the one in my computer to die (in over 20 years of building my computers I have only had 2 power supplies fail on me .. I have replaced many for bigger/better/newer reasons).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Funciona muy bien con todos los componentes aquí comprados en Amazon. El product es muy silencioso y casi que ni se escucha. Si eres alguien novato puede que tengas muchos problemas con los cables y el manual. Yo le pedí ayuda a un familiar y entre lo dos lo pudimos armar después de 3 horas y leyendo el manual detenidamente.Hasta el momento ningún problema con 3 meses de uso constante.Estos son los componentes que usé con esta fuente de poder:Board: GIGABYTE B550M DS3H ACProcesador: AMD Ryzen 5 5600XRAM: Corsair Vengeance RGB Pro SL 32 GB (2 x 16 GB) DDR4 3600MHzSSD: Samsung 970 EVO Plus SSD 2TB NVMe M.2HDD: Seagate BarraCuda - 8 TB, 3.5 pulgadas, SATA 6 Gb / s, 5400 RPM, 256 MB cachéGráfica: GIGABYTE GeForce RTX 4060 Ti Eagle 8G, 3 ventiladores WINDFORCE, 8 GB 128 bits GDDR6

Esta claro que por el precio podrías comprar una psu con un poco mas de voltaje. Sin embargo, la marca be quiet se caracteriza por el desarrollo de buenas fuentes de poder y ahora que tienen la certificación platino sobre todo esta serie straight power 11 la hace muy atractiva y es totalmente modular. El nivel de ruido es muy silenciosa, aunque no tiene la tecnología de zero fan mode, pareciera que lo tiene integrado el ventilador no se oye en lo absoluto. Respecto al 850w probablemente fue un poco de overkill ya que planeo meterle una 3080 y un ryzen 7 o 9 aun esperando la zen 3. pero tener un poco extra no hace daño y te deja espacio para futuras upgrades.Recomendada si quieres una alternativa a una corsair rmx (caracterizada por silenciosa) y con certificación platino.

La compré porque hice una mejora en mi computadora que requeriría más energía y va muy bien y sin ningún problema en el funcionamiento. La única dificultad encontrada fue que las barritas de metal de la parte del ventilador que fungen como "malla" se sienten no muy resistentes, en mi caso batallé 1 poco para meterla en mi gabinete ya que sentía que se podían romper; aparte, el switch para prenderla se siente distinto (por no decir que de menor calidad) que el de la PSU que tuve anteriormente ya que se siente algo "flojo".

La utilizo para darle poder a mi PC con un i9-12900k y no he tenido ningún problema, es muy silenciosa. Próximamente veré cómo se desempeña añadiendo una RTX 3080 TI.Recomiendo que utilicen la herramienta de calculadora de fuente de poder que está en la misma página de be quiet! para que elijan la versión correcta.
No hace absolutamente nada de ruido, hace honor a su nombre, es pequeña así que no es muy difícil ponerla, su nivel de material se ve premium, vale totalmente lo que cuesta
Está bien pinshi hermoso. Tengo algunas dudas, de como conectar algunos cables. Pero aún así, al ponerlo en mi PC funciona excelente. Es mi primer armado. Me encantó el nivel de calidad
